<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                    <head>No. 323.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Brigham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-22"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 22,
                            1886</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 46.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch No. 45, relative to
                        the imprisonment of Mr. A. K. Cutting, I have to inform you that the
                        Department recognize with much satisfaction the justice of your action and
                        the ability you have shown in your report to us of the case.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>ALVEY A. ADEE,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>